    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In the United States presidential election, people who are chosen by each state, usually through an election by individual voters, to represent citizens of the state in casting a vote for leaders; this system is contrasted to an election determined by direct popular vote.</Note_Text>
